\fs34 Create a network
\fs28 \
    Fellow instructions in http://codex.wordpress.org/Create_A_Network\
    Basic steps including:\
    1.1 Install latest WordPress (3.5.1)  and configure database parameters.\
          Disable all plugins.\
    1.2 Open up wp-config.php and add this line \
             /* Multisite */\
       define('WP_ALLOW_MULTISITE', true);\
            above where it says /* That's all, stop editing! Happy blogging. */  \
       \
    1.3 The previous step enables the Network Setup item in your Tools menu. Use that menu item to go to the Create a Network of WordPress Sites screen.\
    1.4 Go to Administration/Tools/Network Setup to create a domain-based network\
     1.5 Add the specified lines to your wp-config.php file\
          define('MULTISITE', true);\
          define('SUBDOMAIN_INSTALL', true);\
          define('DOMAIN_CURRENT_SITE', 'www.bbg.gov');\
          define('PATH_CURRENT_SITE', '/');\
          define('SITE_ID_CURRENT_SITE', 1);\
          define('BLOG_ID_CURRENT_SITE', 1);\
      1.6 Add the specified lines to your .htaccess file in wordpress root directory\
          RewriteEngine On\
          RewriteBase /\
          RewriteRule ^index\\.php$ - [L]\
\
          # add a trailing slash to /wp-admin\
          RewriteRule ^wp-admin$ wp-admin/ [R=301,L]\
\
          RewriteCond %\{REQUEST_FILENAME\} -f [OR]\
          RewriteCond %\{REQUEST_FILENAME\} -d\
          RewriteRule ^ - [L]\
          RewriteRule ^(wp-(content|admin|includes).*) $1 [L]\
          RewriteRule ^(.*\\.php)$ $1 [L]\
          RewriteRule . index.php [L]\
\
